@lepicekmichal We are not planning to implement `ConfigureLogging` to allow users to pass in a `Logger` from outside. Normally a `Logger` applies to a class and works within the class context for tagging reasons.  It does not make sense to keep passing a single instance of `HubConnection` logger from `ConfigureLogging` to other classes as you'll end up losing the logs context due to a single tag. 

We are, however, planning to change SignalR to start using a simple string for log tagging rather than the full package name plus class name.  

We will change all the loggers to use the following format: ` Logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger("SignalR.<ClassName>")`.  Example for HubConnection class: ` Logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger("SignalR.HubConnection")` We hope that proguard/obfuscator will not mess up with that string and you should be able to process logs with `SignalR.<ClassName>` prefix. Let us know if this will work for you.

